post_text:
Buckeye Union High School District Board Meeting
Monday, September 14, 2020 | 6:30pm
1000 E. Narramore Ave Buckeye, AZ

The Board Meeting will be available virtually or in-person.
Join the BUHSD Board Meeting (Public Stream)
https://live.myvrspot.com/player?udi=YnVoc2Q%3D&c=YnVoc2Qx

If you wish to participate in the Call to the Public, but will not be attending the meeting in person, you may email your Call to the Public remarks to Leslie Doud at Ldoud@buhsd.org by noon on the day of the meeting and the remarks will be read for you during the meeting. When submitting a Call to the Public in this manner, please put Call to the Public in the subject line of the email. In the body of the email, before your remarks, please put your name, your phone number, who you are representing, the date of the meeting, and the topic of your remarks.

March 14, 2020

Dear BUHSD Community,

The Governing Board of the Buckeye Union High School District held an emergency Board Meeting at 2:00 P.M. today and approved the closure of the District‚Äôs schools until further notice. The District will continue to monitor the situation. As new information becomes available, we will update you. In the meantime, District staff will be finalizing strategies to continue instruction to students and the final plan will be communicated to parents and students as soon as it is available.

Sincerely,
Eric Godfrey
Superintendent
Buckeye Union High School District

post_text:
Incident at Estrella Foothills

In the interest of transparency and keeping families informed, we want to inform you immediately of an incident that took place today. EFHS Administration received information through our Anonymous Alerts system stating a student had a weapon on campus. The student was immediately located and isolated from other students without incident. It was confirmed that the student was in possession of a firearm and knives. The student was removed from campus and the investigation is being handled by the Goodyear Police Department. This was an isolated incident and students are safe. For these reasons, the normal school day has proceeded without interruption.

post_text: At the end of the school day, there was a report of a natural gas smell on campus. In order to ensure the safety of the students and staff at Buckeye Union High School, the campus was evacuated. The Fire Department and Southwest Gas were contacted and quickly began investigating the campus for any potential gas leaks. No leaks were discovered by the Fire Department or Southwest Gas. The emergency plans of the District and first responders were handled expeditiously and appropriately. The District wants to thank the Fire Department and Southwest Gas for their thorough check of the campus to keep our students and staff safe. All school classes and activities will resume immediately. Again, no gas leaks were discovered and the campus is safe and can resume all activities. Thanks.

shared_text:
Buckeye AZ Police Department
May 4, 2017 at 1:40 PM ¬∑

Today, May 4, 2017, Members from the Buckeye Police Department (as well as a member from city council, fire, water dept, and Youngker High School Cross Country team) participated in the 2017 Special Olympics Law Enforcement Torch Run along side Special Olympic Gold Medalist, Nick Borek. Buckeye PD completed 10 miles for our leg on the run from the Buckeye Police Department (100 N Apache Rd) to Cotton Ln on MC85. Yesterday we received the torch from the Department of Corrections Lewis Prison, and after completing our run we passed the torch onto Goodyear Police Department. The final leg will be run tomorrow where the torch will be presented at the 2017 Summer Games Opening Ceremony at the Kellis High School in Glendale.

Thank you to Argentos Pizza (805 E. Monroe Ave) for donating lunch to all our participants and volunteers. Owner, Tommy also participated in the Torch Run with Buckeye PD.

shared_text:
Buckeye Union High School - BUHSD #201
January 17, 2017 at 7:29 AM ¬∑

Your BUHS AFJROTC Air Rifle team battled this past Saturday for the AZ Air Rifle JROTC Championships. We came just bit short in defending the state title we won last year, as Flowing Wells HS from Tucson beat us by several points, but State Runner-Up is not too bad. Individually however, Buckeye has 2 of the top 3 shooters in the State of Arizona with Carlos Villar coming in on top as the Individual State and Air Force shooter. Matthew Jakubowski made a tremendous comeback and finished 3rd in State after starting in 6th position during the final shoot-off. As usual, Dallas Keck and Cynthia Sutterfield shot their consistent scores. Next, we will be leaving for Las Vegas on the 8th of Feb to compete in the JROTC Regional Championships. Please congratulate these cadets when you see them, and thank you once again for your support to our programs.

post_text: The district is aware of the peaceful protest adjacent to our campus today. In regards to the reasons they protested you will have to ask the organizers. The district is working with staff, local leaders, and black lives matters representatives to develop a plan to turn the incident involving the black lives matter T-shirt from a negative situation into a positive learning experience. This is an excellent opportunity to teach tolerance, understanding, and acceptance for the diverse learners that make up BUHSD. This will be a process and not happen overnight. It will take the support of all involved and from the communities we serve. BUHSD is committed to the success of all students.
